comment:
It is amazing to me that her original lawyers back in Dec 2019 subpoenaed the LAPD for body cams from both sets of officers (specifically citing the 911 call log numbers).  

Then the California Judge agreed with Depp Team to quash or narrow the scope of her neverending 40+ subpoeanas she issued back then--A tornado of subpoeanas.  As a result, the LAPD Body Cam sub got lumped in that pile and became moot.  

Late 2020 Amber's lawyers file a Pitchess Motion to get personnel records on the first two officers hoping to see if there had been any complaints against them, reprimands, not completing training, etc (which was DENIED).  

Then just just this year her newest lawyer re-issues the new subpoena specifically asking for ONLY the first two officers.   After all this, the LAPD apparently has said, oh by the way, do you still want that body cam footage we found that you asked for back in 2019--of the second two officers.  bahahahahahaha!
